inn1.comm: good start by Chatara by pitching it outside off on length, decent carry to the keeper as it's left by the batsman
a bit shorter and wider, Finch takes off for a quick single by tapping it towards cover and even gets an overthrow
short of length again and that's been dispatched to the midwicket boundary! Finch rocked back and pulled it by getting some time with some power
angles it in from short of length outside off, Finch hops back to defend it back
length delivery with a bit of outswing, pushed to point
on length just outside off, Finch defends towards cover
gets him uncomfortable with the bounce by pitching it on length on off and it took the top of the bat
nearly a leading edge as it pitched on middle and leg and went towards slip
solid defence this time off the back foot on the off side
back-foot defence again after the ball turned outside off
touch shorter and Hughes stays back to push it to cover point
tossed up on middle, Hughes leans forward to defend it. Nyumbu starts with a maiden
short and wide and Finch has enough time to cut off the back foot between point and cover point for four. It was in the air but well in the gap
better delivery - length delivery towards off stump and Finch defends it on the leg side
rocks back this time to block the length delivery outside off
plays on the up again, it pitched on length outside off with a bit of shape and went in the air but between short cover and mid-off
fuller on leg stump, pushed down to mid-on for a quick single
fullish outside off and driven firmly to cover

oh, he's bowled'im! Nyumbu pitches it outside off on length, not much flight there, and it spun in, finch played for more turn and was beaten. He didn't use his feet much and was probably caught in two minds. And Nyumbu broke into a jig again!
turns it a long way from outside off down the leg side as Clarke looked to play with the turn, good take by Taylor behind the stumps
outside off again, Clarke goes back and defends on the leg side
tucks this one to deep midwicket with the turn to get off the mark
shortish outside off, rocks back to cut it to backward point
beautiful length outside off, Hughes waits for it to turn and pushes it
on length and well outside off and he lets it go
shorter and still wide, pushed off the back foot to extra cover
angles it in this time towards the stumps, Clarke tucks it to midwicket
full and around off, Clarke pushes it back and Chatara stops it with his right hand in his follow through
full again and a touch wider, pushed a bit wide of mid-off for one
he cuts the short of length ball late past gully from outside off and gets off the mark
tosses it outside off, Hughes replies with a sweep to deep backward square leg
comes down the track and turns it with his wrists to deep midwicket
flighted around off, he presses forward to block it
tries the sweep againa and misses this time as the turn beats him
flighted on middle and leg, he leans forward to block it back
flatter and straighter, nearly goes through but Hughes manages it to get his bat down just in time and survives
pretty full outside off and Clarke drives it to cover point at the edge of the circle
short and wide this time, cut with the bottom edge to short cover
length delivery with a bit of shape outside off, pushed to cover
full on middle and leg this time, driven straight to mid-on where there's a fumble but no time for a run
full on leg again, tucked away to deep fine leg with the angle for two
better line - towards off stump from length, Clarke defends it to mid-on
slightly short and wide, cut off the back foot to backward point off the back foot
keeps low this one after pitching on length and Hughes pushed it to cover
slightly straight on off stump, Hughes turns it towards midwicket for one
on middle and leg, tucked behind square on leg side with the turn
troubling Hughes - bounces off length outside off and went in the air before falling well short of cover point
on off stump and a touch shorter, he cuts off the back foot this time
starts with one on leg stump and Clarke puts it away rather easily off the pads to the midwicket boundary for four
back of length just outside off, Clarke defends it towards point
on length and coming in a touch, Clarke drives it to short midwicket
banged in again outside off, Clarke defends off the back foot to short cover
he goes for the drive but the seam movement off length outside off takes a thick inside edge to go to the leg side. Looked like a wobbly seam there
wider outside off this time and Clarke runs it down to third man for one
comes down the track and tucks it with the turn to midwicket for a quick single
full on the leg stump and Hughes flicks it off the pad to deep midwicket for two
tossed up outside off, rocks back to cut but it hits silly point
goes on the back foot again and cuts it late to short third man
on the leg stump again and Hughes is happy to drive it between midwicket and mid-on for two more
tossed up outside off, cuts it off the back foot to backward point
starts with a shortish length outside off, Clarke swats it down to long-off
turns it in from outside off, Hughes helps it behind square on the leg side
sees some flight and sweeps it from off for one
touch shorter on leg stump, tucked away to square leg after the turn
flighted outside off, drives it with the turn to mid-on
uncomfortable length just outside off and Hughes looks to defend but is beaten by the turn and gets one on the pad
comes down the track and clears the infield with the drive. He didn't middle that one but got two
sharp turn as Clarke goes back and it turned a long way from outside off to go down the leg side off the bat

he's been done by the spin and the sweep doesn't work this time! It was flighted on length just outside off, Hughes swept against the turn and an edge flew back towards slip where Nyumbu took it towards his right. He looked uneasy against the spinners right from the start
comes down on the first ball and defends it from outside off to cover
uses his feet again and defends it back to the bowler this time
goes back this time for the shorter delivery and it keeps low, thick edge goes behind square on off and he's off the mark
right on the middle stump, Bailey leans forward and blocks

and another, and what a beauty from Williams this time! Bailey stood outside the leg stump and exposed the stumps for the delivery that drifted in with the angle but spun enough to beat the outside edge as Bailey played inside the line off the backfoot. The Zimbabwe spinners are putting their team on top as Bailey looked back in disbelief seeing that ball turn
full on the leg stump, Maxwell blocks it back
beaten outside off as Maxwell looks to push it on off
length delivery outside leg, he sweeps and is hit on the pad
full on the leg stump again, thick outside edge goes to point
back of length outside off, tapped to deep backward square leg with the turn
on length outside off, he leans forward and defends
short this time and Maxwell is not going to spare these! He rocked back and smashed it to the midwicket boundary where there's nobody in the deep for four
fuller outside off, pushed down to long-off
bit of flight on middle and leg, helped with the turn to deep fine leg off the pad
turns in from length outside off as Maxwell takes a step forward and is hit on the pad
appeal for lbw, not from the bowler though, it hit him after the turn in front of middle but pitched outside leg
on middle stump now, Clarke blocks it back
similar length on the middle stump, he defends on the off side again
outside leg this time, Clarke takes it on the pad

oh Clarke's lucky to get away with that! He went back to pull the short ball but it turned a long way outside off and he withdrew his shot, the ball took a thick edge and went in the air just wide of first slip
beats him outside off this time by pitching it on length and with the turn
fullish outside off, driven towards point where a misfield from Chatara concedes a run
flatter and straighter on leg stump, tucked towards midwicket
beaten on the drive! Maxwell came forward and drove this one outside off but it didn't turn and went with the angle from round the wicket
shorter this time and Maxwell tucks it off the hip to deep fine leg
comes down the track and plays a cross-batted heave to deep midwicket
lobs off the pad after pitching on leg stump and the crowd cheers as leg slip catches it
low full toss outside off is pushed down to long-on
short of length outside off, Maxwell reverse sweeps it to backward point
touch shorter and flatter, it comes in and Maxwell helps it to short fine leg
flat again outside off, Maxwell cuts hard and gets a thick outside edge which runs away to the boundary to the third man area
edged and put down! He was beaten outside off as he looked to drive, the edge went off the keeper on the pitch and he jumped forward but couldn't catch it on second attempt

knocked him this time, Maxwell also gone! Maxwell also plays inside the line for this ball that pitched outside off and came in, but it didn't come in that much and enough to hit the top of off stump as he looked to push it down the ground by closing the face of the bat
flighted well outside off, cut off the back foot to backward point
gets closer to the ball outside off and blocks it back
pitches it fuller outside off and he sweeps it to deep fine leg
oh, put down again! Marsh flicked it with the turn from outside off to backward short leg where Mawoyo put down the low catch
flighted outside off, he comes forward to defend it
fuller outside off, he leans forward and blocks
on the leg stump, tucked to the leg side towards midwicket for one
beaten with the turn! Pitches it on middle and that turns sharply to beat the outside edge
once again! This pitched a bit closer to off and beat Marsh's edge with the turn again
on middle and leg, pushed down to mid-on
defends against the turn and thick edges goes towards cover
fuller on off stump and he defends it back to the bowler
that's a little shorter which allows Clarke to stay back and tickle it behind square leg
lovely flight just outside off, Marsh lunges as far forward as he could and looks to flick into midwicket. Struck on the pad, but outside the line
a little too much turn down the leg side and that puts him on the umpire's bad side
stays back to a flatter delivery and punches to short cover. Practices the same shot, with that straight bat a couple more times
nips down the track but he can't quite get to the pitch. Doesn't mind wearing it on the pad having gone so far down and with short leg behind fine

mid-off dives over it! That was a gorgeous stroke, especially with the ball turning and bouncing. Didn't over hit it, but he did ensure he was up to the pitch of it so that hitting against the turn wasn't a bother
hammers a sweep fine and is helped by the man at 45 degrees misfielding
slow turn from Williams, Clarke guides it towards point
shuffles back to protect all his stumps and defends a good length ball on off
lovely flight and drift, and Clarke battles it by keeping his front foot away and pushing down to long-off
goes back having seen the ball not tossed up and tapped it to wide mid-on
good stride forward and he kept bat and pad together to defend a flighted ball on off stump
gets back and slaps a shortish delivery to point. Assured footwork from the Australia captain
tossed up outside off, Marsh has to make sure he can get to the ball and smother it to midwicket
lunges forward and sweeps from outside off stump, lbw out of the picture and he brought his bat down from above to avoid top edges
nip down the track with his lightning feet and whips it to deep square leg from virtually miles outside off stump
swept from outside off again and this time Marsh has managed greater timing on the stroke. Deep square leg has his task cut out, and he does well
flighted and drifting away outside off, Marsh eases it towards cover point
employs that sweep again, but the ball was a touch quicker. Couldn't adjust his bat swing and was struck on the pads, well outside the line of his stumps
that's poor. Offers up a juicy full toss and Clarke has whipped it away through a diving square leg. The man in the deep though produces a better effort
good flight and the line is outside off, luring Clarke out onto his front foot to block carefully
flatter and still outside off, flicked into midwicket
that's a half-tracker and Clarke uses the turn and hammers a pull to deep midwicket. Quick switch onto the back foot after pressing forward
tossed up a little closer to off stump and the angle makes Marsh play a little across the line. Gets struck low on the pad, but the deviation would have taken the ball down
flatter in length, but the line is decent. Marsh though gets in line with it outside off
shuffles across to a good length ball and tucking it into the leg side
another solid sweep shot, with Clarke planting his front foot outside off and rolling his wrists to keep the ball down. Square leg though disappoints
flighted and drifting in on middle, Marsh nudges it towards square leg
loses his length and this one drifts a little too straight too, Marsh gets on one-knee and gives some work to deep fine leg
goes down the track and towards the flight of the ball outside off, smothered towards midwicket
holds the length back and seems to pitch it where Clarke doesn't know whether to go forward or back and his guide to third man is beaten. Well bowled, Nyumbu
starts with another low full toss and Marsh has drilled it down the ground - right at Clarke. Struck on the ribs to give Brendan Taylor behind the stumps a sheepish little laugh
flighted outside off, Clarke is up to the challenge with a dead bat
tossed up just outside off, Clarke plays with he turn and works to midwicket
gets deep in his crease and turns it away behind square leg. Lovely footwork and he has picked the gap well enough for a quick single
this one doesn't turn, rather like the one that got Maxwell. Marsh though has a bigger reach and manages to get an outside edge to short third man
flighted just outside off, Marsh smothers it down the pitch
jumps down the track and having reached the pitch he has his pick of areas. Goes for deep midwicket and his timing is quite tasteful. Good enough to force Nyumbu to misfield in the deep
short ball on middle, Clarke pounces on it. Doesn't bother with timing this time, it was just murdered behind square leg. Sumptuous footwork again
pushed through just outside off, but Clarke plays the length and whips it to deep midwicket
gives the ball a little more air and that means it grips into the deck and turns quite considerably. Pitched outside off and hit on middle, but that would have slid down though. Terrific ball
allows the batsman to get on his back foot and tickle a length ball off his pads
tossed up around the off stump, defended carefeully
shuffles back and across on off stump and bunts a good length ball at his feet
deftly sweeps another good length ball just outside off stump to deep fine leg
not quite full enough to draw the batsman forward and Marsh works it away to midwicket, who makes a diving save
this time the length affords Marsh a little more time to pick the gap between square leg and midwicket
that's delightful. He saw the line outside off, he saw the length on the shorter side. Almost immediately made room and late cut it fine of short third man
flighted and angled in on off stump, turned to square leg
gets back to a reasonably fuller ball on middle, was right in front of all three stumps but he managed to tuck it to backwards short leg
gets down the track, but he doesn't force it. Tapped to the right of the bowler
roaring turn there, pitched around off stump and then veered well past Marsh's flick. Umpire Dar says that's too much
rapped down the ground as it is a touch shorter, and doesn't turn as alarmingly
flighted on off stump, Clarke whips it down to long-on
good length around the off stump, Clarke's straight bat gives long-on a work out
a little nip in off the deck to put Marsh in some discomfort. Manages to bring the bat down as quick as necessary and whip into the midwicket region
fullish but a little too straight, Clarke leans over his front leg and whips to the right of midwicket. Mawoyo dives and refuses the single
pushed down the ground

not the pitch to be driving throuh the line and Marsh learns it the hard way. He'd refrained from doing that against the spinners but couldn't replicate that with a little more pace on the ball. It was the cross-seamer, pitched full and a shade outside off, stopped on the pitch just enough to skew his timing and short cover makes a smart grab
back of a good length on off stump, defended solidly
flighted on middle and off, Clarke uses his feet and flicks to long-on
gets back to a reasonanbly fuller ball outside off and defends with an open face
gets forward this time as he sees the ball on leg stump and pushes back at the bowler
got him to play forward again, grip and turn for Utseya forced the batsman to play uppishly through the vacant leg slip area
jumps down the track but doesn't manage to connect the flick, kisses the pad to help him evade a stumping
dances down again, and is struck on the pads again. Second time that the flick has failed Clarke in succession
stays on the back foot to work a good length ball way to square leg
fullish on middle stump, might have straightened a touch too. Haddin keeps faith in his defensive blade
angled in on middle and leg, Haddin has nudged it to short midwicket
fullish on off stump gets a solid forward defensive from Haddin
sneaks in a shorter one that has Haddin up on his toes to tap into the turf by his feet
invites the drive and Haddin employs a checked one to mid-off
loopy delivery just outside off, Clarke takes it on the full and sweeps to deep fine leg. Another over from Waller begins with a full toss. That's Australia's hundred
pushed through on middle and leg, Haddin waits on it and whips past short leg
flighted just outside off, Clarke leans forward and works the ball to midwicket
reads those short ones quite quickly, shifts his weight back and pulls to deep square leg.
flatter ball but the line is the saving grace as Haddin defends on off stump. Looking for the one that skids on, is Waller
a little flighted just outside off, Haddin keeps to his crease and turns to short leg
think he rolled his fingers down that. Clarke likes the length on it though, shorter and outside off. Guided away to deep third man
helped off his hips as Tiripano strays short and a touch too straight
back of a length and angled in at the body, Clarke whips it away to deep square leg to complete a resolute fifty on his comeback from injury
pushes him back but Haddin uses soft hands to dab the ball into the off side and his partner, dodgy hamstring or not, pinches a single.
tucked away behind square leg as he gets up on his toes to ride the bounce on a shorter ball
back of a length on middle and off, Haddin meets it under his eyes
flighted just outside off, Clarke reaches forward to block
gets back and acorss on off stump to ride a flatter delivery through to deep square leg
that's the straighter one and Haddin could only read it off the pitch, shuffles across to off stump and opens the face. Soft hands help him get off strike
lunges forward on his front foot and sweeps strongly to deep square leg
stays back to a good length ball, waits for it to turn and blocks on off stump

dropped and he didn't even get a hand on it! Gave the ball a little more air on middle and that lured the big shot. But Waller's not quite turning the ball as much as the other spinners. That fetches a top edge that almost goes straight up. Waller runs after it himself towards the mid-on region but he is too slow. Misjudged it completely and realises he has to dive, but still couldn't make it
tossed up and angled in on off stump, Haddin attempts a forward defensive and sees the ball rip past his outside edge
again! That's impressive turn as he lures Haddin forward, forces him to play and then weaves the flighted ball well past his outside edge
a touch quicker to push Haddin back, a little more bounce takes the outside edge but soft hands ensures it falls short of slip
a little shorter again but Haddin is wary of the turn now and goes back to tap the ball into the off side
flighted just outside off, haddin eases it to long-off
backs away and cuts a good length ball towards cover
tossed up on off stump, Haddin reaches forward to tuck away to short midwicket
goes back to a good length ball and turns it to the right of short midwicket
a lot quicker that time, Clarke wanted to use the pace and glance it fine but the turn beats him. Wided by the umpire
gets down the track and drills a loopy delivery from outside off to long-on
shortish and pushed through on off stump, turned away to square leg
nicely flighted outside off, Haddin drives watchfully to the right of cover
hits a good length just outside off, Haddin stays back to block to point
even when he bowls quicker, it grips into the pitch and turns quite bit. Clarke was set up for the cut, but a little more turn than he expects flummoxes his timing
keeps to his back foot to work the ball against the turn wide of long-on
goes back and is struck rather high on the pads, that had him squared up but perhaps was just turning past off stump
pushed through on middle and off, Haddin defends
backs away to a good length ball on off stump, tries to steer it behind point but doesn't succeed
jumps back on his middle stump to use his wrists and work a good length ball to square leg
full and angled in on leg stump, Clarke swipes it to deep square leg and looks quite comfortable doing it

length ball, but it comes in slower off the deck. Forces Haddin to mistime his slog. Chigumbura at short midwicket attempts  to run-out Clarke for backing up too much but to no avail and it becomes overthrows as well
that's been threaded through the covers. it was overpitched and Haddin made it worse by making some room and clattering it on the fielder's right
smacked back at the bowler with the full face, that's been hit quite powerfully. Harsh to call that a drop but Chatare is quite disappointed
backs away again and slaps a good length ball down the ground to long-on
that's the shorter slower ball, Clarke had loaded up for the pull and has to adjust his bat swing. Single to deep midwicket.
going down the leg side, Haddin pads it on the back foot
goes back again and pushes to cover after the turn
loud lbw appeal as Haddin came forward for the length delivery on middle and leg and was hit in front. That was nearly plumb
beaten by the turn as Haddin defends with his bat behind the pad and the turn deceives him
goes back and pushes to cover after the turn off the back foot
makes room and drives the full delivery to long-off
short ball and pulled, that went in the air but fell well short of deep midwicket
slow and low full toss on the stumps, pushed down to long-on and they run two very quickly
coming in from outside off, pushed on the off side off the front foot
straight delivery driven down the ground to long-off and they are coming back for the second, which makes it uncomfortable for Clarke's hamstring. He's holding it for a bit now
goes for a heave for the short ball but it doesn't bounce as much and wasn't too far from the off stump
makes room and tucks the incoming delivery to deep midwicket for one
short and flat, pulled to deep backward square leg and they take only one because of Clarke's injury
another one dropped! It went very high behind the keeper on the leg side after taking the leading edge, Utseya had pitched it up, Chatara ran to his right from short fine leg but spilled it
fuller on middle and leg, tucked to deep midwicket for one
full on middle and leg, defends to the leg side
shorter and turning in, helped to short fine leg
flatter and fuller, helped with the angle towards backward square leg
pitches it up and Haddin counterattacks! Went down on a knee and launched this one from leg stump to the cow corner boundary for a clean six!
punched off the back foot after the turn to cover
makes room and this one is chipped just over point and cover point, another lucky one for Australia
that's the most casual appeal you'll see for anything! Taylor caught the ball after it turned away from Clarke, who looked to cut, and Williams politely asked the umpire who shrugged his shoulders
touch fuller, Clarke tries another heave and misses
fuller on middle and leg, slogged to wide long-on for one
comes down the track and nearly yorks himself, he's looking more uncomfortable with his hamstring
makes a bit of room, doesn't middle it, but cuts it between point and short third man for two
wicket falls straightaway! It pitched on length outside off and Faulkner went back to run it around third man but managed a thick outside edge and Nyumbu took a good low catch going down to his right
presses forward and defends it back
flighted outside leg and it's flicked to deep midwicket for one
flighted on the leg stump, pushed towards midwicket for one and 150 comes up
he cuts and gets a bottom edge to the keeper after the bounce, no chance for a run

this time it's gone through! Pitched on length outside off and turned it in, Starc played for a bit of turn in an attempt to push it down but left a wide gap between bat and pad and the ball found that big enough to go through and hit the stumps
tossed up outside off, pushed towards point
leans forward again and is beaten this time by the turn
slightly fuller and drives it and short cover dives to save it
fuller on leg and easily tucked away to the leg side, Haddin responds well for the call for two and an inaccurate throw helps him
full toss outside off, pushed back to the bowler
shorter and flatter on the stumps, pushed it to midwicket for one
slower through the air and turning from outside off, tapped to midwicket
fuller outside off and Cutting defends it back to the bowler
turns in from length outside off, Cutting defends off the backfoot
charges down and punches it to long-off for one
fullish outside off and pushed back to the bowler
full on the pads and it runs down to deep fine leg. Oh they're coming back for the second, a bit of a mix up between the batsmen but they are safe
short ball and Cutting smashes it with a pull to the midwicket boundary for four! Australia will probably look to attack the seamers
back to full length, turned with the wrists to the leg side
back of length and coming in, runs it down by opening the face of the bat for a four to the third man area
angling in again, from length this time, tucked towards midwicket for an easy single
slightly flat on the leg stump, goes for a slog and misses
rocks back to the back foot and punches it to cover point where Tiripano dives to his left full length and saves a few runs
he charges down and powers it over the umpire's head for four! Didn't allow that one to turn or bounce at all and took it on the full
goes back this time and tucks to deep fine leg for one
short anf flat going towards leg, tapped to square leg for one more
flighted outside off on length, Cutting sees it through to the keeper as it turns in
full and wide but Haddin smashes it straight down the ground with a swish and that goes all the way before hitting the sight screen
low full toss, pushed down to long-on for one
short ball outside off and it's pulled away to the left of deep midwicket for two in the gap
tries the block hole and it's lofted down the ground to long-on after a bounce
slower bouncer cuts in from outside off and Haddin hooks it for one
full on middle and leg, heaved to deep midwicket for one. 12 runs from that over
slower bouncer and that's swatted wide of deep midwicket for one

pitched up and that's where Haddin wanted it! Gets the middle of the bat and tonks it to the midwicket boundary by coming close to the ball for six! That hit an ad board and the fielder at deep midwicket caught it after that
makes room on the other side now and drives it down to long-off
another full delivery, another six! This was well outside off and right in the zone for Cutting to loft it with some power over the long-off boundary
slower ball from back of length, pulled to the leg side and the 50 partnership brings up the 200. 50 off 33, by the way
slower delivery cutting in, Haddin made room to pull but it came in a lot and he eventually left it, crammed for room

they are asking for the run out, decision has gone upstairs. Cutting drove the full toss down to long-on and came running back for the second, the fielder does well to throw it to the keeper's end but Taylor has not collected it. But the ball deflects off is gloves and hits the stumps, catching Cutting nearly out of the frame. Cutting has to go back
almost a legspinner from outside leg, whipped to deep fine leg for one
full and wide, Haddin chases it a bit and tries to cut but misses. Looks to the umpire to see if it's a wide but he's unmoved
he holes out this time! It was pitched up again around leg stump and he lofted it down to long-on for an easy catch. But he did his job for that crucial knock of 49
can Lyon hit it? He does, all the way for six. Full on the stumps and Lyon tonks it over the square leg boundary to make sure Clarke's effort to comes back counts
full toss outside off and Lyon targets the leg side again, gets one to the midwicket are

inn2.comm: starts with a length delivery outside off and angling away, he lets it go
on the stumps this time from length, Mawoyo defends by leaning forward
on length and swinging in late from outside off, another leave
length delivery on the middle stump with some inswing, he defends it back
angles it away this time, Mawoyo leans forward and lets it go
angling away again from the batsman from length, easy leave for Mawoyo and that's a maiden
outswing from Marsh after pitching it outside off, Raza watches it go to the keeper
bit of outswing again from back of length outside off, Raza defends off the backfoot
on length this time around off and shaping away, Raza defends towards cover
charges down the track wide of leg stump but the ball pitches well outside off and swings away further, out of his reach
half volley outside off with outswing, driven to point without much footwork
nips it in this time from length towards off stump, Raza defends off the back foot
good carry to the keeper from length outside off, Mawoyo leaves carefully
touch shorter outside off and he guides it late with the angle to third man to get off the mark
loud lbw appeal, not given! It pitched right on middle and was swinging in and Raza misjudged it and left it completely, to be hit on the pads but it bounced too much and was probably going down leg
pitched around off on length and angles away, close leave from Raza
gets the width and cashes in, and crashes it for four! Well outside off and Raza leaned towards it to drive it with some power through the covers for four
makes room and gets a full delivery around off, drives it down to mid-off
from back of length around off, Mawoyo stays back and defends
slightly wards middle and leg, Mawoyo plants his front foot forward and closes the face of the bat to defend it on leg
leans forward again for this one on length outside off and defends. There's a small appeal for run out as the fielder gave the ball to Haddin who hit the stumps, but Mawoyo was back in time
fullish on middle and leg, driven to midwicket on the move
towards the pads again, tucked to deep fine leg for one and that's Mawoyo's highest score of the series
angled towards middle and leg again from length, Raza defends it to mid-on
full delivery with the angle way outside off, Mawoyo chased and missed and that was nearly a wide
just around off this time, forward defensive to short cover
shorter delivery now angling away, Mawoyo tried to steer it over the slips but missed again
pitches it outside leg this time and he runs it down to fine leg for one
full on the pads and Raza drives it off the back foot past midwicket for two
length delivery to end the over outside off, Raza lets it go
fullish on off stump, Mawoyo drives it back to the bowler, could not middle that one
full on the pads and Mawoyo flicks it on the up to deep backward square leg in the gap for two
back towards off stump, he defends it back again
goes straighter outside off from length, he leaves it for the keeper
slightly back of length outside off and Mawoyo cuts it late and delicately to third man
seaming in towards off stump from length, Raza blocks it on the off side
back of length just outside off, plays it down with soft hands to third man for one
pitches on off and goes away with the angle, dangerous leave from Raza and Starc has a few words to say to the batsman again
that's how Raza likes to hit them - make room by getting the front leg out of the way and over the infield on the off side. This full delivery is dispatches over mid-off
makes room again but this one pitched outside leg and he gets an inside edge onto his pad. Starc continues his one-sided conversation with Raza
further down the leg side and this one's a wide
right on middle stump, Raza goes back in the crease and defends it towards cover. He wanted the single but was sent back by Mawoyo
back of length now, Raza wasn't expecting that and nearly gave a catch to point by playing it early off the back foot. It bounced once before point and this time Starc talks to Raza with a smile
back of length outside off, Mawoyo cuts and nearly gets an outside edge to the keeper. The extra bounce did him
angles it in a bit from back of length, defends to cover point
angles it in further towards middle stump, he defends it back
short and wide this time and Mawoyo connects this time! It went in the air and there were sounds of 'catch it' but it went to the left of point
brings it in from length, Mawoyo presents a forward defence
back of length now from outside off, pushed to point off the back foot
it's pitched up and Raza likes them there! Full and wide and he launches it with a straight bat over mid-off for a one-bounce four
back of length now around off, he goes on his toes to defend it on off
bangs it in again on off, hops back to defend it towards cover
angles it away now from outside off, Raza lets it go
back of length and width on offer, cuts it past point to third man for one
tries the yorker and it's full outside leg, goes to fine leg for a leg bye
edged and just past the keeper! Short of length outside off, Raza looked to run it towards third man but it took a thick edge and just cleared a flying Brad Haddin
short of length and angling in, defends on the off side
angled in from length, he defends it on the pitch on the front foot
short ball outside off and Raza pulls it, nearly losing his balance, to midwicket
makes room and charges down, pushes the delivery to cover point
full on the pads and it's flicked away for two on the leg side, misfield at midwicket allowed them the runs
back of length around middle and leg, he stays back to defend
strays down the leg side and it's gone down to fine leg off the pad
it's that back of the hand slower ball from Faulkner, but it's down leg for a wide
short of length outside off, steered past a diving point for one
down the leg side for another wide - that was a bouncer and Faulkner thought there was bat on that
quicker and more accurate bouncer and he ducks under it this time
length delivery towards middle and leg, defends it back to the bowler
on leg stump and goes down with some bounce for a wide
he goes back an defends the ball on leg after the turn
spinner gets a wicket, who else? It turned in sharply from outside off, Raza went back to cut and the bounce got a thick outside edge for an easy catch to first slip
shortish outside off, he defends on the off side
stifled appeal as Masakadza tries a heave off the flighted ball but it was going down leg
fuller outside off, he drives and gets an inside edge onto the pad
much fuller and wider, he leaves it alone
full and outside off, firm drive straight to cover
angled in this time from length, Mawoyo replies with a solid defence
short ball going down leg, Mawoyo chases with a hook but it's a wide
full on off stump, driven back to the bowler who gets a hand to it
bouncer angled in very sharply towards the batsman and he does well to sway out of the line
slow and short, a leg cutter, pulled past midwicket for one
back of length outside off, tapped towards point off the back foot
goes back to steer the ball to leg but it doesn't turn that much
loud appeal for lbw but the ball pitched outside off and as he padded it, it struck him pretty high on the pads
gets him this time! The ball comes in from outside off, Mawoyo doesn't have much room but he wants to cut it and gets an inside edge onto the off stump. Lyon gets another
tossed up outside off and Taylor sweeps it fine down leg with a big stride and gets off the mark with a four
taps to midwicket for a quick single and makes it in time
tossed up on middle, Taylor defends
slower through the air on middle and leg, Taylor works it towards the vacant square leg region
good length ball on off stump, Masakadza stays to the crease and punches it back down the pitch
sees a little more flight and gets into the sweep, didn't time it as well enough though. Australia though that was off the pad
looped up, perhaps a little too much. Driven to long-off
stands up tall and punches towards extra cover, but Finch himself races after it and sends in a throw that makes the batsman duck for cover

flighted outside off, Taylor likes that length though as he lunges forward and sweeps him past the right of the short fine leg. All along the ground, and he beats deep square leg as well. Prompts Bailey to move him finer
goes back to a good length ball, that was slower through the air. Good job he got bat to that
flighted outside off, nudged to short leg
tossed up just outside off, gets forward and blocks
goes back seeing this a touch shorter and tries to turn it around the corner, short leg dives to his right to stop it
lovely flight and drift outside off, Taylor works it to the right of mid-on
nicely flighted on middle, Taylor blocks
goes back and punches a shortish ball through extra cover
that's the risk you take with a part-timer, it's short, it sat up and it's been massacred over long-on. Pure power
fires it in quick and flat on leg stump, Masakadza is up for it as he tickles it to short midwicket and races across to the other end.
mid-on is still in the circle, and Taylor takes advantage this time. Tossed up on middle, he clears his front leg and hoists him for a one-bounce four
encore, and this has been timed even better. No bother to keep it down as he got the pitch and launched the overpitched ball into the long-on boundary
tossed up outside off, Masakadza kicks it away and weathers an optimistic appeal
a little too much flight there as he searches for some rip, ends up offering exactly what Masakadza wanted a she laces a drive through extra cover with great authority
pulls the length back, but it is still slower and it grips into the deck and loops up off the inside edge, front pad and falls a few yards short of the onrushing short fine leg

huuuge appeal, twin stage appeal but Lyon does not get his man. This was tossed up around off stump and then turned in to strike him low enough on the pad. The umpire through is wary of the turn and the stride forward and says no
good length ball probing his middle and leg stump, Masakadza shuffles across and tickles it away to short leg
lunges forward on off stump to defend and wears it on the pad again. Another appeal, another denial.
pushed through on leg stump, tucked away behind square leg
flighted on leg stump, Masakadza gets down on one-knee and sweeps it quite fine, so much that it deflects off the keeper's gloves
goes back to defend a good length ball that doesn't turn a lot
another paddle with no short fine leg. Didn't worry about hitting the flighted ball on leg stump in the air either
flatter and quicker on middle, Taylor shuffles across and tickles in front of square leg
flighted on off stump, Masakadza eases it into the covers
a little flatter in length and its been tapped down the ground
flighted on off stump, draws Masakadza out of his crease but since he cant get to the pitch, he defends
stays back and flicks a good length ball away to deep square leg
leans forward and clips a tossed up delivery past the right of short leg, it was in the air though.
realises this wasn't pitched up and hugs to his crease, strong wrists clips the ball away to long-on
good footwork from Taylor, went right back on off stump to tap the ball on top of the bounce between short leg and leg slip
wristy, very wristy as this was pitched up outside off and dealt with to deep midwicket
flatter and quicker on off stump, easy decision for Masakadza to stay back and tuck to midwicket
flighted a bit more outside off, he drives to cover
this angle from around the wicket might be stifling, but not quite putting the batsman in any discomfort. Easy ticked to midwicket
this hits the footmarks on leg stump and turns away further quite sharply. Masakadza simply watches it and his team enjoys five wides
flicks away off a good length to square leg
finds a good length and it goes on with the arm. it was the line that troubled the batsman, pushing on outside the off stump
flighted on and around leg stump, Masakadza shuffled across and pushes his bat in front of his pads
serenely played. There was leg slip, there was a short fine leg but they were both useless as Taylor sweeps along the ground and well past their reach
tossed up a lot more on middle, defended calmly
looped up outside off and Masakadza reaches for it with a defensive bat and pushes into the covers
thats Zimbabwe's hundred, and the crowd like it. So does the coach, if those slow claps are an indication. Pushed to long-on
good length ball, quicker on middle, tucked away through midwicket
stays back to tickle a shortish ball off his pads, but this time he finds short fine leg
shortish and just a shade outside off, tapped down into the off side
off stump toppled! He's been beaten for pace! This was quick, it was on target, with a hint of nip back in. Masakadza's defence is loose as his bat leads far past his body and is cut in half
full and sliding across the right hander, driven into the covers
stays on the back foot and eases a short of a good length ball to cover point
back of a length, teasing for the outside edge. Waller isn't forthcoming as he hoists his bat high above his head
fuller and outside off, Waller allows it to sail through to the keeper
flighted on middle, he leans forward and flicks through midwicket
goes back, watches the turn and plays with it to short leg

you little beauty! He's got through Taylor and off stump gets a thwack again! Gorgeous loop on the ball which lured Taylor as far forward as he could, but then it dipped on him and sneaks between bat and pad as he goes for a flick. He was so off balance that he needed to pull one hand off the bat to steady himself on the pitch
and that ball brings them all into play. Good length ball on off stump but he stays back to block
defends from the back foot
brings him forward with a flighted delivery that is eased towards mid-off
back of a good length on off stump, defends solidly enough
shortish and outside off, Waller chases after it with a cut and is beaten
goes with an off cutter and the direction is good. Waller is pushed back and blocks
back of a length and a shade outside off, defended
that's another ripper from Starc, hits the deck and seams away past the outside edge with Waller forced to hang his bat. Lovely line and the captain appreciates it from first slip
good length ball outside off, watchfully left alone to the keeper
those three men around his bat, right in his eyeline, means he knows there's no one at third man. Reaches out as he reverses the grip on his bat and clubs him to the third man boundary

what a catch! Clarke, take a bow! That was tossed up on off stump which elicits a little more bounce to ruin Williams' reverse sweep. It takes the glove, flicks the keeper's gloves and Clarke leaps to his right and clings on to a stunner over his head
leaves them all in his dust as he jumps down the ground and hammers a flighted delivery away to long-on.

forces Lyon to pull his length back and that changes the batsman's plans as well. Settles into a defensive push, but the turn beats the inside edge to hit him on the pads. Too much turn for the leg before appeal
jumps down again and lifts the tossed up delivery over long-on. Surveys it with a bit of disdain

how did that miss! Haddin can't believe it either and it ends up two byes! That nearly shaved off stump as he went back, thinking the ball was short enough to cut. It might have been, but the turn removed any room required for the shot. Chigumbura surviving on the edge here
good length ball just outside off, left alone
back of a length and outside off, not quite far enough to entertain the cut that Waller goes for. Beaten
gets the ball to nip back in a little bit, the defensive push ends up an inside edge towards square leg
short of a good length on off stump, Chigumbura keeps it out of his stumps
back of a length and going on with the angle across the right-hander, tapped away behind point
pushes it fuller on off stump, and Chigumbura makes a late decision to block it.
flighted outside off and it invites the drive through the covers, gets an inside edge to mid-on
again, lures the cover drive again and it ends up an inside edge onto pad. Dangerous shot with the dip and turn of Lyon on this pitch
flights it even further outside off and Waller pushes with his hands into the covers
whips a slower, flighted ball from outside off to mid-on. Lyon's slower pace almost deceived him enough to lob to the man
shorter and quicker on off stump, Waller's far more comfortable with the block
back of a length and outside off, steered towards point
good length on off stump, Chigumbura blocks resolutely
back of a length and on off stump, Chigumbura uses an angled face to tap the ball square on the off side
brings this one back in off a fuller length, just about enough to gain the inside edge from Chigumbura. Single towards fine leg
fuller and pushed across Waller, who wants nothing to do with it
shortish on off stump, Waller looks for a single towards point but he steers it straight to the fielder. That off side ring is swooping quite ferociously.
strays down the leg side with a good length ball.
that's been a regular occurrence, sweeps a flighted ball from outside off all along the ground to deep square leg
a little more bounce on a good length ball that Waller tries to tickle fine
gets back and pulls on one foot to deep fine leg, a little too short from Lyon on that occasion
gets down the track to work a tossed up ball to deep midwicket. They look for two, but Marsh is on the ball too quickly
flighted just outside off stump, he gets forward to block
backs away and cuts a shortish ball into the covers, ends his spell with a dot ball. Changed the game on its head and trots off to field in the deep.
pokes at a short of a good length ball outside off, low percentage shot and he realies that as he is beaten
again, this is closer to off stump, demanding that he plays. Chigumbura is tentative and that lack of intent beats him.
banged in a little too short, Chigumbura slaps it in front of point as hard as he can
good length ball on off stump, Waller gets forward to block
ventures fuller in length, Waller watches it carefully and pushes down to mid-off. He's trying as hard as he can, but he's had a difficult outing with the bat today
full again on off stump, he sets up for a punch down the ground but can't beat the fielder at mid-off
flighted on leg stump, picked away through midwicket, who is now being brought up in the circle
goes back to assess the turn off a flighted ball outside off, rides it to short fine leg
drops it short and Waller has scooped it over square leg. He's starting to display a little more aggression
tossed up on middle, Waller whips it away to deep midwicket
tossed up outside off, Chigumbura caresses it through the covers for a couple of runs
flatter but on the pads, he goes back and flicks with comfort to deep square leg
shortish and outside off, Chigumbura stands up tall and punches to cover
keeps to his crease and guides a short of a good length ball to third man. Neatly done
shuffles across on off stump and taps the good length ball to mid-on
that was a touch slower on middle and off, Waller nudges to midwicket
the legcutter this time and he beats Waller all ends up. Wonderfully disguised and pushed fuller on off stump, lures Waller to chase after it with an angled face. Not far away from off stump either
picked up the short ball early and pulled it straight of midwicket. No real timing, but there was enough to clear the circle
backs away and taps a short ball through cover point. That's not the length a spinner should be bowling on this pitch, even if Maxwell has switched over the wicket. Clarke wasn't happy at slip either
that's better, earns a clap from his captain as he flights the ball on off stump and keeps the batsman to a forward defensive
tossed up on the stumps again, a lot slower, Waller blocks
that's his best shot of the day. Enjoys the shorter length, makes some room outside off and cuts it to the left of cover. Pummeled

throws his head back in agony as he he gifts his wicket away! That was slower again from Maxwell, tossed up outside off. He tried to work it with the turn towards midwicket, but the ball grips enough to make him lob a simple catch back
he comes round the wicket and fires it on the stumps, the batsman defends
bowls a length ball on off, punched to cover
he comes forward and defends this one straight down the pitch, off the inside half of the bat
shorter delivery from Cutting, the batsman waits on the back foot and steers it to third man
he comes forward and defends the length delivery solidly to point
he gets into a tangle as he fends at this shortish delivery, it hits the handle of the bat and lobs up behind him.. a little to the left of Haddin. They take a quick single
back of length delivery outside off, he cuts it down to third man for a single to keep the strike
the sliver hammer continues from round the wicket, the batsman nudges it towards short fine leg
they love it, they all love it! This is beautifully hit through cover. Maxwell looped it outside off and served the half-volley and Chiggy was on to it
on the stumps this time, the batsman defends to the leg side
some turn and it hits the pads, but this was heading down leg side
he waits on the back foot and punches it back to the bowler
he is not able to thread this through off, hits it to the fielder at cover and loses strike for the next over
starts off with a widish length delivery and Tiripano leaves it alone
quick and it cuts slightly away from the batsman to fizz past the outside edge
drifts on to the pads and Tiripano gets cheered for bringing Chiggy back on  strike with a flick to fine leg. That cheer could have been for Zim reaching 150
this is angled too far away from the batsman. Aleem Dar gets some stretching excercise
fuller delivery on the stumps, the batsman squeezes it out towards point  and calls for a quick single
shortish delivery on the stumps, the batsman chops it to the right of first slip
rolls his fingers on this fuller delivery but Tiripano goes well to keep it out, defends it down the pitch
he pushes this in the air off the back foot, wasn't too far from midwicket threre
fuller delivery on the pads and Chiggy goes for a sweep but misses, gets hit on the pads
waits in the crease and nudges the pushed through delivery to square leg for a single
he has got a leg slip in place for Tiripano but pushes it too far outside off, the batsman is able to run it down past first slip for a few runs
a reverse-sweep attempted! But he he just kills the ball on the pitch..too full
comes forward and defends the fuller delivery to off
he waits on the back foot and runs the back of length delivery down to third man for a single
he chops it on to his middle stump! Chiggy's trusted Tiripano's batting but he gets cramped by the angle from round the wicket, looks to defend off the back foot but gets a thick inside edge
angles this too far down the leg side, one run less off the target for Zim
shows some solid front-foot defence, pushes it to cover
more solid defence. He needs to do more of this to help Chiggy out here
oh hello! Short and wide and Utseya is not going to let that go unpunished.. Whacks it through point with a powerful cut shot

appeal for caught behind as Haddin takes this down the leg side, there was some noise as the ball went past the batsman.. Dar calls it a wide.. but it looks like it might have flicked something on the way
fuller on the pads, Utseya keeps strike with a clip down to fine leg
defends this down the pitch
stays on the back foot and punches it to long on for a single
stays back and works it away to deep square leg for a couple as Faulkner fumbles
he clips this to short fine and briefly thinks of a single, but turns it down
he comes forward and punches this solidly down the pitch, straight to the bowler
he walks down the pitch and flicks the fuller delivery to midwicket
angles in this one from wide of the crease and Prosper flicks it nonchalantly off his hips to fine leg
he comes forward and defends the length delivery to point
he leans forward and punches this on the up to deep cover for a single
cracks that really hard off the front foot! But he has found the man at point.. A meter here or a meter there, that would have run away
he wants a single off the last ball with a push to cover, but turns back in time as Maxwell gets to it
tossed up on the stumps, pushed to midwicket
he whips it off his toes to square leg for a single.. but another fumble .. Lyon this time.. and they come back for a second
pushed through on the stumps, defended to midwicket
he uses his feet and drives this one wide of long on to pick up another couple

he was in trouble there! Drives the half-volley straight to mid-off and sets off for a single.. Turns back and has to dive to get back in.. A little straighter throw would have had him. It was a full-length dive.. Just gets back in time.
flatter on the stumps, he picks up the single to square leg to keep the strike
here is the first one.. Chiggy waits for this length ball and just opens the face at the last moment to run it down past the keeper.. A bit of an outside edge but this looked like it was intended
short of length delivery on off, the batsman hops on the crease and defends
the slower bouncer outside off, the batsman watches it go through the keeper.. Aleem Dar thinks it's high enough for a wide.. and rightly so
shortish delivery on the stumps, he clips it behind square for a single
well done Prosper.. he comes forward and defends
go white ball go, the crowd seems to be egging it.. Prosper opens the face to place this push beautifully in the gap at point..
gets on top of this shortish delivery and chops it to backward point
he looks to run this down to third man but this zips past the outside edge
marginally short! Utseya had his eyes at the gap at midwicket and he pulls it hard through the region.. Deep square leg has to run around and slides to keep this in.. Excellent placement from Utseya
length delivery outside off, Chiggy is calm as he pushes this back to the bowler
fired on the blockhole, dug out down the pitch

here comes the back of the hand slower delivery and Faulkner - and everyone- goes up in appeal for an lbw.. but then he has overstepped big time. But prior to that he had flicked the stumps, which was why it was called a no-ball. No free hit for that
slower delivery on the stumps, the batsman is foxed by it but defends it down the pitch
he comes forward and punches it firmly to the off side but Bailey dives to his left to prevent the single
it's running away.. This is blasted through cover off the front foot. He hit it on the up.. The man from deep cover has to run a long way to cut that boundary off
fuller delivery outside off and Utseya slices it behind point.. This is getting close to the boundary but Cutting dives to save a couple
length delivery on the stumps, loud cheers as Utseya nudges it to square leg for a single. You would think these are being smoked for sixes here.. it's loud.. it's energetic
fuller on the stumps, Chiggy comes forward and defends.. The man is not panicking..
length delivery on off, the batsman comes forward and pushes it to cover
a misfield at backward point by Maxwell gives another single.. This was a slower ball and it was just pushed softly.. He lets it bounce under his hands..
back of length delivery on off, the batsman defends it calmly to the off side
he reaches his half-century with a punch through cover point! Raises his bat..the crowd knows the captain is their hero... they are all behind him
that's an excellent yorker and it somehow misses the off stump.. the batsman was too late to bring the bat down
whoa!!! Mid-on is up and as soon as Faulkner serves up the length ball, Prosper hammers it over the infield.. they are not going to let this go
a slower slow very slow yorker, the batsman digs this on the pitch
slower bouncer, the batsman looks to upper cut it but makes no contact
full and on the middle stump, the batsman pushes it to mid off
superb delivery! Slower, flighted, grips the surface and turns past the defensive prod
slower and on a length, the batsman cuts this one hard but finds the man at backward point
what a corker! Where was he hiding all this while? Tossed up, and it turns and bounces past the shoulder of the bat.
some width outside off  and Chiggy punches it to deep cover to bring the 200
tossed up on the stumps, Utseya flicks it through cover for a single ..
Bailey almost pulls off a blinder at cover! Dives to his right but just couldn't slide his finder underneath this.. It was a high full-toss and the batsman ended up lobbing it towards short mid-off
fuller delivery, sliced to point. No runs this time

swings at this full delivery and gets a solid piece of wood on that.. He was  aiming for downtown Harare, but gets it behind deep square leg off the inside half.. The fielder saves the boundary.. but the match is slipping away
fires in a good old-fashioned yorker, not much one can do about it
another good yorker, this time it is steered down to third man for a single
U T S E Y AAAAAA! Smokes it over deep midwicket for a massive hit.. Zimbabwe have beaten Australia after 31 years...!!!
